COMPETITOR #2: HUBSPOT SALES HUB
================================================================================

OVERVIEW
--------
- Strong in inbound/marketing-led sales motions
- Popular with SMB and growth-stage companies
- Typical pricing: $90-120/user/month (Professional/Enterprise)
- Strength: Ease of use, marketing integration, freemium funnel

WHEN WE WIN
-----------
✓ Complex B2B deal cycles (HubSpot built for transactional)
✓ Advanced forecasting needs
✓ Deal intelligence and scoring
✓ Enterprise security requirements
✓ Sophisticated reporting and analytics

WHEN WE LOSE
------------
✗ Marketing and sales tightly integrated (HubSpot's strength)
✗ SMB with simple sales process
✗ Already using HubSpot Marketing Hub
✗ Strong preference for all-in-one platform

KEY BATTLEGROUND: DEAL COMPLEXITY
---------------------------------
HUBSPOT: Designed for velocity sales. Works great when deals are small
and cycle times are short. Struggles with multi-threaded enterprise deals.

VELOCITYRM: Built for complex B2B. Stakeholder mapping, MEDDPICC tracking,
multi-quarter deal management, expansion revenue tracking.

TALK TRACK:
"HubSpot is fantastic for certain sales motions - especially inbound and
velocity deals. Where we see teams struggle with HubSpot is complex B2B sales
with multiple stakeholders and long deal cycles. VelocityRM was purpose-built
for that complexity. How would you describe your typical deal?"

LANDMINES TO SET:
- "Ask HubSpot how they handle multi-stakeholder deal tracking."
- "Ask about their forecast accuracy metrics."
- "Ask how they manage deals that span multiple quarters."

