================================================================================
GENERAL COMPETITIVE TACTICS
================================================================================

1. DISCOVERY FIRST
Don't lead with competitive comparisons. Understand their needs, then position
against what matters to them.

2. NEVER BADMOUTH
"They're a good company, but here's where we're different..."
Negativity reflects poorly on you.

3. USE SOCIAL PROOF
"We've won a lot of deals against [competitor]. Here's what customers tell us
made the difference..."

4. KNOW THE OBJECTIONS
Every competitor has a common defense. Know them and have responses ready.

5. DEMO TO YOUR STRENGTHS
When competing, structure your demo around capabilities where you win.

6. LANDMINES WORK
Plant questions they should ask the competitor that expose weaknesses.

